<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REASSEMBLE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="11">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, place the plunger stop in the LO-reverse shift yoke block, and
                install the spring in the bore of the yoke and onto the shank of the plunger (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b7">Figure 117</hotlnk>). Install the plug and tighten to compress the springs.
                Back the plug out 1 to 1-1/2 turns and stake the plug through the small hole in the yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b7">inset</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029b7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029b7" filename="../figg13/G13029b7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 117. Install Spring and Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the housing in a vise with the front of the housing to the right (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b8">Figure 118</hotlnk>). Install 3rd-4th speed shift bar in the bottom bore with
                detent notches to the front, installing the yoke, lockscrew and safety wire.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029b8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029b8" filename="../figg13/G13029b8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 118. Place Housing in Vise</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Keep bar in the neutral position during installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>DO NOT EXCEED the recommended torque ratings for yoke lockscrews as over-tightening may
                        distort the shift bars.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install interlock ball in the vertical bore of the front web (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b9">Figure 119</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029b9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029b9" filename="../figg13/G13029b9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 119. Install Interlock Ball</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air valve shaft in the vertical bore in the rear web (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c0">Figure 120</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c0" filename="../figg13/G13029c0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. Install Air Valve Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install actuating ring and clip on the air valve shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c1">Figure 121</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c1" filename="../figg13/G13029c1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. Install Actuating Ring and Clip</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st-2nd speed shift bar in the center bore and install shift yoke on the bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c2">Figure 122</hotlnk>). Insert interlock pin in the detent notch (inset).
                Install lockscrew and safety wire.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c2" filename="../figg13/G13029c2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 122. Install Shift Yoke on Bar and Insert Interlock Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install interlock ball in the vertical bore of the front web (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c3">Figure 123</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c3" filename="../figg13/G13029c3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 123. Insert Interlock Ball</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install LO-reverse shift bar in the upper bore, detent notches to the front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c4">Figure 124</hotlnk>). Install yoke on the bar, fork to the rear, and install
                lockscrew and safety wire.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c4" filename="../figg13/G13029c4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 124. Install LO-Reverse Shift Bar in Upper Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise. Install the three tension balls, one in each bore on the
                housing top (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c5">Figure 125</hotlnk>). Keep yokes in neutral.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c5" filename="../figg13/G13029c5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 125. Install Tension Balls</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the three tension springs, one in each bore, in the top of the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c6">Figure 126</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c6" filename="../figg13/G13029c6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 126. Install Tension Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the tension spring cover. Tighten the bolts to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m)
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029c7">Figure 127</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029c7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029c7" filename="../figg13/G13029c7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 127. Install Tension Spring Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
